{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1769630331,"nonce":"j+1Lqx4DbGzv/cdWZgDwgbHB4Jo=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87mf_ZG","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/111","origin":"github"},"title":"Add GitHub labels metadata for agent discoverability","message":"## Problem\n\nWhen creating issues via `gh issue create`, agents must guess valid labels. Invalid labels cause command failure, requiring retry.\n\n**Example from Session**:\n```bash\ngh issue create --label \"enhancement\" --label \"infrastructure\"\n# Error: could not add label: 'infrastructure' not found\n```\n\nThis creates friction:\n- Agent must retry without label\n- No way to discover valid labels programmatically\n- Manual trial-and-error required\n\n## Proposed Solution\n\n### Option 1: Static Metadata File (Simplest)\nCreate `.agent/github_metadata.json`:\n```json\n{\n  \"labels\": [\n    \"bug\",\n    \"documentation\",\n    \"enhancement\",\n    \"good first issue\",\n    \"help wanted\"\n  ],\n  \"updated\": \"2026-01-28\"\n}\n```\n\n**Benefits**:\n- ✅ Quick to implement\n- ✅ Easy to query\n- ✅ Version controlled\n\n**Drawbacks**:\n- ⚠️ Must be manually updated when labels change\n\n### Option 2: Helper Script (Recommended)\n```bash\n# .agent/scripts/gh_create_issue.sh\n# Validates labels before calling gh CLI\n# Falls back to fetching labels if metadata missing\n```\n\n**Benefits**:\n- ✅ Validates before submission\n- ✅ Can auto-fetch labels on first run\n- ✅ Better error messages\n\n### Option 3: Auto-Generate on Status Check\nUpdate `status_report.sh` to cache labels:\n```bash\n# Fetches labels periodically and caches to .agent/scratchpad/\ngh label list --json name \u003e .agent/scratchpad/github_labels.json\n```\n\n## Implementation\n\n**Recommended Approach**: Combination of Option 1 + 2\n1. Create static `.agent/github_metadata.json` with common labels\n2. Add `gh_create_issue.sh` helper that validates against metadata\n3. Update `CLI_COMMANDS.md` to document the helper\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Agents can discover valid labels without trial-and-error\n- [ ] Invalid labels are caught before `gh` call\n- [ ] Documentation shows how to add new labels\n- [ ] Metadata is easy to update\n\n## Priority\n\n**Low-Medium** - Quality of life improvement, not blocking.\n\n---\n**🤖 Authored-By**: `Copilot CLI Agent`\n**�� Model**: `Claude Sonnet 4.5`","files":null}]}